{"body": "I'm sorry but I particularly don't see a real gain with this refactor, since the `Options` class is only used by the scope method to wrap some method calls, instead of using the options hash directly, and afterwards the hash is used again to set `scope[:options]`. At the end, seems that just using the options hash is clear enough.\n\nAnyway, thanks for your patch :)", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6050601", "created_at": "2012-05-31T23:54:45Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6574#issuecomment-6050601", "updated_at": "2012-05-31T23:54:45Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6574, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238066fbd3543c15100c8f7"}, "id": 6050601, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6574"}
